The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, July 05, 2004 				 Martyrs
																								Chandigarh, July 4: Panjab University is offering free education to the children of Kargil martyrs. Apart from the tuition fee, the university will also waive admission, examination and hostel fees. 																								Public relations director Sanjiv Tiwari said the decision was taken at yesterdays meeting of the university syndicate. This is the least we could do for the Kargil martyrs, he said. 																								In 1999, about 474 soldiers laid down their lives trying to push back Pakistani intruders in the Kargil, Drass and Batalik sectors of Jammu and Kashmir. 
